label.value: normal subtelomeric chromatin knob formation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the formation of chromatin knobs in subtelomeric regions is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Chromatin knobs are highly condensed chromatin bodies formed from subtelomeric heterochromatin (observed on chromosomes 1 and 2).

label.value: decreased subtelomeric chromatin knob formation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the formation of chromatin knobs in subtelomeric regions is decreased. Chromatin knobs are highly condensed chromatin bodies formed from subtelomeric heterochromatin (observed on chromosomes 1 and 2).

label.value: normal protein localization to chromatin at boundary element IRC1L

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at the IRC1L boundary element is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to chromatin at boundary element IRC1L

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at the IRC1L boundary element is abolished.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to chromatin at boundary element IRC1L

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at the IRC1L boundary element is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal histone H4-K16 acetylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 16 of histone H4 is abnormal.

label.value: decreased histone H4-K16 acetylation at boundary element IRC1L during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 16 of histone H4 at the IRC1L boundary element occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: decreased histone H4-K16 acetylation at telomere during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 16 of histone H4 in telomeric regions occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H4-K16 acetylation at telomere during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 16 of histone H4 in telomeric regions occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: normal RNA localization to nucleus

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of an RNA to the nucleus is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal telomerase holoenzyme complex assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which telomerase holoenzyme complex assembly is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal telomere-telomerase complex assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which telomere-telomerase complex assembly is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abnormal telomerase RNA reverse transcriptase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of telomerase RNA reverse transcriptase activity is abnormal.

label.value: decreased telomerase RNA reverse transcriptase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of telomerase RNA reverse transcriptase activity is decreased.

label.value: normal DNA recombination frequency at subtelomeric heterochromatin

value.value: A regulation phenotype in which the frequency of DNA recombination is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in subtelomeric regions.

label.value: abnormal telomerase template activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which telomerase template activity is abnormal.

label.value: increased duration of actomyosin contractile ring contraction

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the duration of actomyosin contractile ring contraction is longer than normal.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to plasma membrane at cell division site during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the plasma membrane surrounding the cell division site is abnormal.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found at the cell division site plasma membrane and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased Tf body formation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nuclear chromatin organization is abnormal, such that regions containing transposons (Tf2 elements) are physically clustered to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: decreased protein-protein interaction during mitotic S phase

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the binding of one protein to another occurs to a lower extent than normal during S phase of the mitotic cell cycle. The relevant proteins may include the one encoded by the mutated gene, or may both be encoded by different genes.

definition.value: This term can be used for any protein-protein interaction that is affected by a mutation, whether or not the mutated gene product is one of the interacting proteins. We recommend noting which proteins were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein targeting to vacuole, with protein secreted

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which protein targeting to the vacuole occurs to a lower extent than normal, and some of the protein is secreted.

definition.value: The difference between this term and 'decreased maintenance of protein localization in vacuole, with protein secreted' (FYPO:0005491) is that this term refers to the initial targeting of proteins to the vacuole, whereas FYPO:0005491 refers to proteins remaining in the vacuole after they are targeted there. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein phosphorylation during cellular response to brefeldin A

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, occurs to a greater extent than normal during a cellular response to brefeldin A.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal viability upon nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which a normal proportion of cells in the population remains viable when cells in a culture are deprived of nitrogen.

definition.value: Use this term to annotate experiments in which a culture is grown to stationary phase under nitrogen-depleted conditions, and then the number of cells viable enough to form a colony upon return to conditions supporting vegetative growth is measured and compared to wild type.

label.value: normal protein level during cellular response to hydroxyurea

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein measured in a cell during a cellular response to hydroxyurea is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to cleavage furrow

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cleavage furrow is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to cleavage furrow rim

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cleavage furrow rim is decreased. The rim is the part of the cleavage furrow closest to the contractile ring.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal single-stranded telomeric DNA binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of single-stranded telomeric DNA binding by a gene product is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). The relevant gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: abolished histone H3-K9 dimethylation at centromere inner repeat during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which dimethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 in centromere inner repeat regions does not occur.

label.value: decreased mitotic cohesin loading

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cohesin loading is decreased during the mitotic cell cycle. Cohesin loading is the topological linking of a cohesin ring complex to chromatin.

label.value: abolished mitotic cohesin loading

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cohesin loading does not occur during the mitotic cell cycle. Cohesin loading is the topological linking of a cohesin ring complex to chromatin.

label.value: decreased mitotic cohesin unloading

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cohesin unloading is decreased during the mitotic cell cycle. Cohesin unloading is the topological unlinking of a cohesin ring complex from chromatin, which negatively regulates sister chromatid cohesion.

label.value: abnormal microtubule bundle

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which the amount, distribution, or morphology of microtubule bundles is abnormal.

label.value: thick stable microtubule bundle

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which stable microtubule bundles are thicker than normal. Stable microtubule bundles, also called Q-MT bundles, are found in quiescent cells.

label.value: thin stable microtubule bundle

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which stable microtubule bundles are thinner than normal. Stable microtubule bundles, also called Q-MT bundles, are found in quiescent cells.

label.value: long stable microtubule bundle

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which stable microtubule bundles are longer than normal. Stable microtubule bundles, also called Q-MT bundles, are found in quiescent cells.

label.value: short stable microtubule bundle

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which stable microtubule bundles are shorter than normal. Stable microtubule bundles, also called Q-MT bundles, are found in quiescent cells.

label.value: long, thick stable microtubule bundle

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which stable microtubule bundles are longer and thicker than normal. Stable microtubule bundles, also called Q-MT bundles, are found in quiescent cells.

label.value: short, thin stable microtubule bundle

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which stable microtubule bundles are shorter and thinner than normal. Stable microtubule bundles, also called Q-MT bundles, are found in quiescent cells.

label.value: abnormal microtubule bundle during G0 to G1 transition

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which the amount, distribution, or morphology of microtubule bundles is abnormal when the cell undergoes transition from G0 phase to G1.

label.value: T-shaped cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a new growth zone forms along the lateral portion of the cell (often in the middle) before septation, such that a single cell grows in the form of the letter T. Cell length is normal.

definition.value: One distinction between T-shaped and other branched cells is that in T-shaped cells the new growth zone forms before NETO. A T-shaped cell may septate perpendicular to the normal septation axis, and divide to form normal-shaped daughter cells. Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'viable cell population' (FYPO:0002058) or one of its descendants.

label.value: T-shaped cell during G0 to G1 transition

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a new growth zone forms along the lateral portion of the cell (often in the middle) before septation, such that a single cell grows in the form of the letter T, when the cell undergoes transition from G0 phase to G1. Cell length is normal.

definition.value: A T-shaped cell may septate perpendicular to the normal septation axis, and divide to form normal-shaped daughter cells. Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'viable cell population' (FYPO:0002058) or one of its descendants.

label.value: abnormal cell polarity

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the establishment or maintenance of cell polarity is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal cell polarity during G0 to G1 transition

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the establishment or maintenance of cell polarity is abnormal when the cell undergoes transition from G0 phase to G1.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to cell periphery during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cell periphery is abnormal.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found at the cell periphery and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to cell periphery during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cell periphery does not occur.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to cell periphery

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cell periphery is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal nuclear transport

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which nuclear transport is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal nuclear transport during meiosis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which nuclear transport is abnormal during one or both meiotic nuclear divisions.

label.value: growth auxotrophic for magnesium

value.value: Auxotrophy in which a cell requires magnesium ions in the medium for vegetative cell growth.

label.value: decreased protein localization to chromatin during meiotic cell cycle

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to chromatin is decreased during the meiotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.
